race.comment: Looks a good race for SET ME LOOSE (10). Was well fancied on debut and hit the ground running, leading until the final few hops before being nabbed right on the line. Can only improve and will take beating again. SMART AND MIGHTY (2) is another long overdue for a win. Beaten just half a length into fourth latest and on the quick back-up. Has the claim and is among the main hopes. STRUM (3) has placed two of the last three, the latest running on hard at Mornington. Drawn for a good run and will find the line strongly.  PULL MY FINGER (10)  has raced three times for three minors, the latest when second over 1000m at Ballarat. Sits just off the speed and in the mix again.
